cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.DB, cs.AI, cs.LG

This paper deals with name matching between multiple natural languages, which involves natural language processing and information retrieval techniques. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a new framework that uses a dictionary and a proximity matching algorithm, which involves database and artificial intelligence techniques, respectively. Therefore, cs.IR (Information Retrieval), cs.DB (Databases), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are also likely sub-categories. Finally, the paper evaluates the proposed framework empirically, which involves machine learning techniques, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) a possible sub-category as well.
